# Latency
## Average Duration

These graphs show the average duration of each lambda in milliseconds.

Not currently showing P95 and P99.

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Message Codes

The number of times each message code has been received per lambda. Does not include STARTED and COMPLETED codes. For credential, this graph does not include the SESSION_CREATED message code. For issue-biometric-credential, it does not include the VC_ISSUED message code.

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
# Saturation
## Concurrency

The number of instances running at the same time per function. The graphs are coloured with RAG.

**Red**: using 100% or more of the lambdas reserved concurrency

**Amber**: using 80% or more of the lambdas reserved concurrency

**Green**: using under 80% of the lambdas reserved concurrency

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
# Latency
## Max Duration

These graphs show the maximum duration of each lambda in milliseconds. RAG is set due to lambda timeout values.

**Red**: longer than or equal to the lambda timeout value

**Amber** longer than or equal to 80% of the lambda timeout value

**Green**: shorter than 80% of the lambda timeout value

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
# Errors
## Message Codes

Left value shows number of STARTED message codes. Right value shows number of COMPLETED message codes.

For credential lambda, the third tile is the number of SESSION_CREATED message codes.

For issue-biometric-credential lambda, the third tile is the number of VC_ISSUED message codes.
